<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF8FF746FF38FB052520FB0F" bold="true" box="[189,561,1175,1206]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF8FF746FF38FB0527E4FB0F" bold="true" box="[189,245,1175,1206]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">The</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF8FF746FF78FB0526C2FB0F" authorityName="Oberthur" authorityYear="1881" box="[253,467,1175,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constantinaria">constantinaria</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF8FF746FE59FB0A2520FB0F" bold="true" box="[476,561,1176,1206]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">group</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF6070DFF8FF746FF38FB5D23D3FA1F" blockId="20.[189,1399,1231,1446]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
The six known members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF8FF746FDC8FB4225E9FB50" authorityName="Oberthur" authorityYear="1881" box="[589,760,1232,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constantinaria">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF8FF746FDC8FB4225E9FB50" box="[589,760,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">constantinaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group are easily recognised by their wing patterns: brown coloured with large deep yellow blotches on the forewing. Male valves are overall similar as in the 
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF8FF746FE94FA8926B3FA8C" box="[273,418,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">parrhasiata</emphasis>
group; the aedeagus is straight and slender without cornuti. The male genitalia within the group are rather similar and appear to be of little use for the diagnosis of species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF8FF746FB7BFAD32267FAE2" authorityName="Brehm" authorityYear="2018" box="[1278,1398,1345,1371]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occulta" status="stat. rev.">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF8FF746FB7BFAD32267FAE2" box="[1278,1398,1345,1371]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. occulta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20E6664FF8FF746FF38FAF5260EFA38" box="[189,287,1383,1409]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">stat. rev.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF8FF746FED2FAF526AAFA39" authority="Brehm, 2018" authorityName="Brehm" authorityYear="2018" box="[343,443,1382,1409]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hiltae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF8FF746FED2FAF526AAFA39" box="[343,443,1382,1409]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. hiltae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20E6664FF8FF746FE47FAF5250DFA38" box="[450,540,1383,1409]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
form a cryptic species complex that can reliably only be distinguished by 
<collectionCode id="ED589FC8FF8FF746FF38FA1E27ECFA1F" box="[189,253,1420,1446]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">DNA</collectionCode>
barcoding. Species are distributed from 
<collectingCountry id="F35E479DFF8FF746FD52FA1E245AFA1F" box="[727,843,1420,1446]" name="Colombia" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Colombia</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry id="F35E479DFF8FF746FC5FFA1E235EFA1F" box="[986,1103,1420,1446]" name="Argentina" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13721B88FF8FF746FBDAFA1E23A5FA1F" box="[1119,1204,1420,1446]" captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[214,1376,264,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[212,1376,264,1900]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Distribution maps. A. The balteata group and Callipia paradisea Thierry-Mieg, 1904. B. The vicinaria group. C. The constantinaria group. D. The parrhasiata group. More details can be retrieved from a Google Earth kml file (Supplementary File 3)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1177135/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
